This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and social media analysis, which are the main topics of the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. The paper also involves unsupervised learning, which falls under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The use of retweet behavior of users suggests the involvement of social network analysis, which is covered by the cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) category. The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) as it aims to discover the stances of people and media on current topics. Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis, which is covered by the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category.
